\par SKILLS SUMMARY
\par }{\fs20\cf0 If you buy a class skill, your character gets 1 rank (equal to a +1 bonus on checks with that skill) for each skill point. If you buy other classes\rquote  skills (cross-class skills), you get 1/2 rank per skill point.
\par Your maximum rank in a class skill is your character level + 3.
\par Your maximum rank in a cross-class skill is one-half of this number (do not round up or down).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Using Skills:}{\fs20\cf0  To make a skill check, roll: 1d20 + skill modifier (Skill modifier = skill rank + ability modifier + miscellaneous modifiers)
\par This roll works just like an attack roll or a saving throw\emdash  the higher the roll, the better. Either you\rquote re trying to match or exceed a certain Difficulty Class (DC), or you\rquote re trying to beat another character\rquote s check result.

\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skill Ranks:}{\fs20\cf0  A character\rquote s numb
er of ranks in a skill is based on how many skill points a character has invested in a skill. Many skills can be used even if the character has no ranks in them; doing this is called making an untrained skill check.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Ability Modifier:}{\fs20\cf0  The ability modifier used in a skill check is the modifier for the skill\rquote s key ability (the ability associated with the skill\rquote s use). The key ability of each skill is noted in its description.

\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Miscellaneous Modifiers:}{\fs20\cf0  Miscellaneous modifiers include racial bonuses, armor check penalties, and bonuses provided by feats, among others.
\par 
\par Each skill point you spend on a class skill gets you 1 rank in that skill. Class skills are the skills found on your character\rquote s class skill list. Each skill point you spend on a cross-class skill ge
ts your character 1/2 rank in that skill. Cross-class skills are skills not found on your character\rquote s class skill list. (Half ranks do not improve your skill check, but two 1/2 ranks make 1 rank.) You can\rquote t save skill points to spend later.

\par The maximum rank in a class skill is the character\rquote s level + 3. If it\rquote s a cross-class skill, the maximum rank is half of that number (do not round up or down).
\par Regardless of whether a skill is purchased as a class skill or a cross-class skill, if it is a class skill for any of your classes, your maximum rank equals your total character level + 3.
